http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/159017321X/braipick-20For?mc_cid=3D=
6c73834c6e&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID] as long as I=E2=80=99ve lived in Brooklyn=2C=
 I=E2=80=99ve had an abiding self-consolation ritual. In troubled times=2C=
 I would head to Prospect Park on my bike and ride along the loop until I=
 felt better. And I always did=2C largely thanks to an old lopsided tree t=
hat stood atop the formidable uphill crowning the final segment of the loo=
p.

This greeter after the lung-splitting climb=2C its own crown the shape of=
 a lung=2C became my beloved friend through life=E2=80=99s trials and triu=
mphs. For years=2C the tree saw me through every heartbreak=2C every bout=
 of ill health=2C every kind of psychic tumult. I was comforted by its con=
stancy =E2=80=94 the quiet certitude with which its barren branches clawed=
 at life as they reached into the leaden winter sky=2C assured of spring=
=E2=80=99s eventual arrival; and when spring did come=2C the unselfconscio=
us jubilation of its new leaves=2C just born yet animated by the wisdom of=
 the tree=E2=80=99s many decades.

Art by Alessandro Sanna from Pinocchio: The Origin Story (https://www.brai=
npickings.org/2016/09/12/pinocchio-alessandro-sanna/?mc_cid=3D6c73834c6e&m=
c_eid=3D[UNIQID])

Even when the grimmest day of my adult life arrived=2C I knew what to do=
 =E2=80=94 I mounted my bike=2C put on Patti Smith talking about William B=
lake and death at the New York Public Library=2C and headed for the park.=
 I circled the loop for hours on end=2C resting by the tree after each clo=
sing climb to savor its silent solace.

I turned to the tree again and again over the years=2C and took many portr=
aits of its various seasonal guises. Recently=2C in the midst of a particu=
larly trying stretch of life=2C I once again sought this steadfast friend.=
 I pedaled to the park hungry for its comfort=2C restless to reach the end=
 of the loop. But when I climbed that final hill=2C my pounding heart sank=
 with heavy stillness.

Where my tree once stood=2C there was now a shallow stump=2C its rings of=
 life bleeding into the open air with the incomprehensible finality of a b=
eheading.

I felt gutted=2C bereft. I thought about the growing body of research on w=
hat trees feel (https://www.brainpickings.org/2016/09/26/the-hidden-life-o=
f-trees-peter-wohlleben/?mc_cid=3D6c73834c6e&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C about=
